IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE ASSOCIATION IS A MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS OF PUBLIC HOUSING AUTHORITIES WHOSE PURPOSE IS TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY AND MANAGEMENT OF ASSISTED HOUSING PROGRAMS THROUS SEMINARS, WORKSHOPS AND THE REPRESENTATION OF PUBLIC HOUSING EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS TO THE DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT (HUD) AND THE CONGRESS OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ASSOCIATION IS A MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION OF EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS OF PUBLIC HOUSING AUTHORITIES WHOSE PURPOSE IS TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY AND MANAGEMENT OF ASSISTED HOUSING PROGRAMS THROUS SEMINARS, WORKSHOPS AND THE REPRESENTATION OF PUBLIC HOUSING EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS TO THE DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT (HUD) AND THE CONGRESS OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA.
IRS990.Desc: THE ASSOCIATION SERVES AS A LIAISON BETWEEN HOUSING AUTHORITIES, CONGRESS, AND HUD. IT PROVIDES TRAINING SESSIONS AND GUIDANCE TO ITS MEMBERS CONCERNING PUBLIC HOUSING REGULATIONS. THE ASSOCIATION ALSO SERVES TO PROMOTE AWARENESS OF NATIONAL HOUSING ISSUES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON THE BEHALF OF CERTAIN PARTICIPATING MEMBERS, THE ASSOCIATION IN CONJUNCTION WITH ANOTHER NATIONAL HOUSING ADVOCACY ORGANIZATION HAS COLLECTED FUNDS TO FINANCE LITIGATION AGAINST THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT. THESE FUNDS ARE HELD SEPARATELY FROM THE ASSOCIATION'S OPERATING ACCOUNT AND ARE OF A PASS-THROUGH NATURE AND BECAUSE OF THAT, UNSPENT AMOUNTS ARE RECORDED AS AN ESCROW LIABILITY RATHER THAN RECOGNIZING REVENUE AND EXPENSES.

THE ASSOCIATION IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION THAT IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER 501(C)(6) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE ASSOCIATION IMPLEMENTED THE PROVISIONS OF FASB ASC TOPIC 740, ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, AS OF OCTOBER 1, 2009. AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018, THE ASSOCIATION HAS NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT QUALIFY FOR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ASSOCIATION FILES AN ANNUAL FORM 990 WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AND ITS TAX RETURNS FOR THE YEAR 2015 AND SUBSEQUENT YEARS REMAIN SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY MEMBERS OF THE FINANCE COMMITTEE PRIOR TO THE FILING OF THE FORM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION CONSISTENTLY MONITORS ITS EMPLOYEES FOR ANY IMPROPRIETY, AND ANY IMPROPRIETY WOULD BE DEALT WITH SWIFTLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S PERSONNEL COMMITTEE APPROVES ALL EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ALL DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR PERIOD.
